    About this item

    • Safe Volume Control for KidsEngineered for young ears, these headphones for school maintain safe levels below 85dB (Study Mode) and 95dB (Travel Mode). Perfect headphones for kids during online classes or noisy commutes, providing hearing protection.
    • Lightweight Comfort for Extended WearUltra-lightweight kids headphones for school with adjustable headband and memory-protein ear cushions. Designed for ages 7-15, breathable materials prevent fatigue during 2-hour lectures or audiobook sessions ideal headphones for kids.
    • Crystal Voice & One-Touch ControlsNoise-canceling mic ensures clear video calls for online learning. Intuitive controls empower students to manage lessons independently essential for kids headphones for school.
    • Tangle-Free & Universal CompatibilityKids headphones with cord feature reinforced nylon braid to survive backpack chaos. 3.5mm jack seamlessly connects to iPads, smartboards, and classroom tablets the ultimate headphones for school.

        3. How did NUBWO come to be?

          In 2015, a group of avid e-sports enthusiasts noticed the lack of affordable, high-quality gaming headsets. This inspired us to launch NUBWO.

          What sets our products apart?

          Our products stand out due to our dedicated innovation and design teams. They continuously research and implement friendly materials and designs in our headphones.

          Why do we love what we do?

          Our passion for e-sports drives us to fulfill our mission of delivering cost-effective, yet high-quality headphones to our users.

        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        Learn more how customers reviews work on Amazon

        Customers say

        Customers find the gaming headset to be good value for money, with nice sound quality and effective audio and microphone functionality. They describe it as comfortable and durable, though some report it breaking after 5 weeks of use. The microphone and noise cancellation receive mixed reviews - while some say it works well, others report poor microphone performance and insufficient noise reduction.

        Amazon Customer
        5 out of 5 stars
        Amazing headset for an amazing price - Detailed review
        I was like the other skeptics here, doubting this headset could deliver my needs. I bought this headset for my daughter so we can play online together. I really didn't want to spend to much but I new buying a headset at Walmart was really gonna screw me over. I just plugged these baby's into my Gigabyte board and it took me less than 5 minutes to shape the sound like I wanted with the Realtek audio manager and let me tell you these things sound super good. Audio is part of my every day job and I've been doing it for many years. If these sounded like crap I would tell you. I personally own the SteelSeries Siberia 840 and I would say that sound quality is hanging right in there with the 840. Of course I didn't really buy the Siberia's for concert quality drivers. It was more about the wireless and Bluetooth capabilities. Don't get me wrong I love my wireless 840 but if I needed to travel I would have no problem carrying the U3 with me. Bass response is very good. You can feel the slight thumps on low end sounds. But it also sounds really tight. Not sloppy bass. Mids and highs come in nice and clear. Like I said before, tune your sound up with your EQ and you will be amazed. The mic is also extremely clear. I get great levels in discord with just the regular mic gain at 100% in windows. Even with a +10db boost it still has very little hiss. Anything higher than that and you will start to get a hiss if you are in a moderately noisy room. The only issue I have with these is that the cup size for my ears is just a hair smaller than I like, though the cup has generous room. I'm so used to my 840's and their big and deep cushions. Spoiled I know :) Also the cups don't swivel so if you plan on leaving a cup off your head for an extended period of time it's probably going to start to get uncomfortable after a while. So overall, get them. If you just don't trust anyone the best part is your only out $16 :D

          5.0 out of 5 stars
          Amazing headset for an amazing price - Detailed review

          Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2019
          I was like the other skeptics here, doubting this headset could deliver my needs. I bought this headset for my daughter so we can play online together. I really didn't want to spend to much but I new buying a headset at Walmart was really gonna screw me over.

          I just plugged these baby's into my Gigabyte board and it took me less than 5 minutes to shape the sound like I wanted with the Realtek audio manager and let me tell you these things sound super good. Audio is part of my every day job and I've been doing it for many years. If these sounded like crap I would tell you.

          I personally own the SteelSeries Siberia 840 and I would say that sound quality is hanging right in there with the 840. Of course I didn't really buy the Siberia's for concert quality drivers. It was more about the wireless and Bluetooth capabilities. Don't get me wrong I love my wireless 840 but if I needed to travel I would have no problem carrying the U3 with me.

          Bass response is very good. You can feel the slight thumps on low end sounds. But it also sounds really tight. Not sloppy bass. Mids and highs come in nice and clear. Like I said before, tune your sound up with your EQ and you will be amazed.

          The mic is also extremely clear. I get great levels in discord with just the regular mic gain at 100% in windows. Even with a +10db boost it still has very little hiss. Anything higher than that and you will start to get a hiss if you are in a moderately noisy room.

          The only issue I have with these is that the cup size for my ears is just a hair smaller than I like, though the cup has generous room. I'm so used to my 840's and their big and deep cushions. Spoiled I know :) Also the cups don't swivel so if you plan on leaving a cup off your head for an extended period of time it's probably going to start to get uncomfortable after a while.

          So overall, get them. If you just don't trust anyone the best part is your only out $16 :D

          5.0 out of 5 stars 5/5 Stars. Would highly recommend.
          Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2019
          Verified Purchase
          Works really great with PS4 console and online gaming! I was a bit skeptical about the headset because of the price and thought maybe the headset might feel weird or perhaps the audio quality was going to be bad, but I am really impressed on the overall quality AND with such a low price it's honestly a deal and worth it! I mostly enjoy the mute and audio volume control located on the chord itself. It's so convenient to lower and raise the volume without needing your TV controller and can actually go fairly loud.
          My buddy has an actual PS4 Bluetooth/wireless headset and honestly he has the most problems with headsets out of anyone. lol. It either loses signal, sounds distorted, or when the charge is going low it sounds extremely choppy. I'm an old school gamer, I enjoy a simple plug in headset and bam! I'm ready to play.

          The other great thing I enjoy is the headset has a one year limited warranty! Even if the headset lasts me a year and a day and I can no longer replace, for what it's worth I will still be satisfied and mostly likely buy another.

          ** Just a friendly tip if using for PS4, if you have the audio settings to "Microphone only" when using the headset and will be using the TV for gaming audio, you will only be able to listen out of one ear. I'm assuming so can hear part TV part headset. I would recommend switching microphone audio to "All Audio". Only then can you hear both gaming and chat audio from both sides of the headset and it's soooo much clearer.**

        • Jim Scott
          5.0 out of 5 stars Best Budget Gaming Headsets on the Market
          Reviewed in the United States on September 17, 2021
          Verified Purchase
          I bought a pair of NUBWO U3 gaming headphones for about $18 each in 2018 after seeing a favorable write up online. My expectations were low due to the price point, but I was pleasantly surprised with the fit, sound quality and durability.

          The headphones were comfortable on my head and on the heads of my children ages 5-11. The sound was surprisingly good with decent bass in it. The mic is clear, although you can sometimes hear background noise. These aren't noise cancelling headphones, but they do a decent job of cutting out external noise.

          My son, who is now 7 1/2, is rough on electronics and his head set lasted almost 2 1/2 years without any issues. It started to short out by the plug in the last month, but honestly I was surprised they lasted this long. By comparison I bought LogiTech G933 gaming headphones for $100 and they broke in 3-4 months with me using them carefully.

          I just bought another pair today for $13 each. One to replace my son's headset and the second to put in the closet in case we need it.

          I'd recommend the NUBWO U3 at a higher price point based on quality, but for $13-18 it's an outright steal of a deal. I'd recommend them for all parents shopping for their kids or for any budget conscious gamers.
